<div class="notice notice-info">
  Unlike if-then and if-then-else statements, the <strong>switch</strong> statement can have a number of possible execution paths.
</div>
<div class="notice notice-info">
  Each <strong>break;</strong> statement terminates the enclosing <strong>switch</strong> statement.
</div>
<div class="notice notice-info">
  <strong>; (Semicolon)</strong> ends a statement, not function declaration.
</div>
<div class="notice notice-info">
  <strong>{ } Braces</strong> are used to group statements and declarations. There must be equal numbers of opening and close braces.
</div>
